message.body: Hello
Hi there! What are you up to?
I'm just sitting at work now
Ur real name django??
No, I'm a huge Django Reinhardt fan. I do a lot of gigs playing his music. Have you heard of him?
No what kind of music
He's European eh?
Thought maybe he was african

Yes, he was a French Gypsy. He played from the 20s to 30s, blending traditional gypsy music with jazz. Two fingers on his left hand were paralyzed aftera fire but he was the sickest guitarist at the time (and arguably of all time).
Yea thats w hat Wikipedia says haha
I'll have to check him out
What r u up too?
Working, like a dog. It's another busy day at LDC!
That's kind of a funny adage - my dog does no work.
U work for LDC?
Yes, though I probably shouldn't tell you any more than that. I think they want to maintain anonymity in the study.
This isn't a conflict of interest??
No, I have nothing to do with the study.
What kind of work do you do?
Oh I see. I am a budget analyst for philly school district
Doin anything fun for memorial day
Ugh, I've been in meetings all day. Budget analyst for PSD? What's your analysis? We're grilling for Memorial Day - classic.
The analysis is that were broke lol
Haha. I hope you didn't have to work too hard to figure that out. Do you know how you're analyses are used? Do you feel like you're making a difference?
*your analyses
I work in a control function. Make sure hr doesn't fill more positions than are budgeted for
I dun make any hard De isions
Do you like your job?
I dun mind it. It can be pretty boring at times
Especially over the summer
But work is work. How do unlike the ldc
You like*
I hear you, work is work. LDC can be really challenging and even frustrating at times, but the work can be really interesting and it gives you a lot of skills and experience.
What do u do for them
I'm a research project manager; I develop/maintain budgets and timelines etc. I also supervise much of the work for my projects.
You deal with budgets too eh?
I can relate lol
Yeah, and we all have the same problem - no matter how you slice it, there just isn't enough to go around!
Somebody's got money. U guys funded federally?
